claim.claim-text:
1. A system for conducting a game for individual participating players at remote locations, the players being telephone subscribers, said game being at least partially conducted by telephone, and for rewarding players who have entered an acceptable answer to a question, the system comprising: 
a recording medium playback facility at a central facility; 
recording media intended to be played back by said playback facility, the media having recorded thereon signals conveying at least one question which is either a single-part question or a multiple-part question and signals defining at least one acceptable answer to a question, an acceptable answer carrying a prize having monetary value; 
telephonic communications means including a telephone facility between said playback facility and players' locations including means operable by a player wishing to play said game for activating said playback facility; 
means for presenting a played-back recording at players' locations; 
caller identification means at said telephone facility; 
means at players' locations for entering an answer to a question in players' telephones; 
an answer evaluation facility connected to players' telephones and to said playback facility having means for receiving entered answers from players' locations and for receiving acceptable answers from said playback facility, said evaluation facility having means for comparing an entered answer to an acceptable answer to identify a winning player's acceptable entered answer; 
means for presenting evaluation and monetary prize results to winning players; and 
means for making a prize available to winning players; 
wherein, if two or more answers are acceptable, one can be a preferred answer; 
wherein a preferred answer receives a higher award; 
wherein said evaluation facility rewards an individual answer essentially immediately following its input by a player; and 
wherein said evaluation facility permits input of a single answer by a player on the spur of the moment.

2. A system for conducting a game for participants at remote locations comprising: 
a recording having recorded thereon at least one question set comprising signals including question signals conveying at least one question in open language, said question requiring an answer given within a defined time period and including answer signals conveying an acceptable answer to said questions, said answer signals being conveyed once during said time period as instructional signals in machine-readable language and once in open language essentially following said time period, to inform participants after they have answered said question, an acceptable answer carrying an award; 
central means for making a recorded or a live announcement of an award to participants at remote locations; 
a central playback facility activatable by a participant at participant's remote location for playing back the signals of said recording; 
means operable by an individual participant for contacting and activating said playback facility to play back the signals of said recording; 
means for transmitting said signals from said playback facility on wire and/or wireless communication means; 
means at participants' locations for receiving said question and answer signals conveyed in open language following said time period; 
means at participants' locations for entering a participant's answer to a question; 
a central evaluation facility having means for receiving said machine-readable answer signals of the recording and means programmable by said instructional signals for recognizing and accepting a participant's acceptable entered answer, said facility having a memory for storing award information, there being means for automatically identifying individual participants who have entered an acceptable answer; 
central means for transmitting information relative to said award to said memory at the evaluation facility; 
means for preventing the entering or evaluation of answers following the allowed time period; 
communication means connecting participants' locations with the playback facility and the evaluation facility; 
means for informing an identified participant of an award; and 
means for making an award available to an identified participant who has entered an acceptable answer; 
wherein, if two or more answers are acceptable, one of said answers is a preferred answer; 
wherein a preferred answer receives a higher award; 
wherein said evaluation facility rewards an individual answer essentially immediately following its input by participant; and 
wherein said evaluation facility permits input of a single answer by a participant on the spur of the moment.

