7. A system for transmitting task-setting program signals from a central site to a plurality of receiving stations at remote sites and for responding to said program signals at said receiving stations, said system comprising: 
central means for transmitting a program signal, said program including a task calling for a prescribed response within a time period allowed for responding; 
central means for transmitting an instructional signal incorporating response criteria defining a prescribed response, an allowed time period and a value assigned to an acceptable response; 
means at each of said receiving stations for responding to a task presented in said program; 
response evaluation means responsive to said instructional signal for determining an acceptable entered response and for assigning a value to an acceptable response; 
means for preventing the evaluation of a response after the allowed time period; 
two-way communication means between receiving stations and response evaluation means; and 
means for informing a respondent of a value assigned to said respondent's acceptable response.

8. A system for transmitting task-setting program signals from a central site to a plurality of receiving stations at remote sites and for responding to said program signals at said receiving stations, an acceptable response carrying an award, said system comprising: 
central means for transmitting a first program signal including a task in the form of a question and a period of time allowed for answering; 
means at each of said receiving stations for presenting a program transmitted by said program signal to members of an audience; 
central means for transmitting a second instructional signal incorporating response criteria for scoring at least one acceptable response, there being a fixed or computed award associated with acceptable responses; 
means at each of said receiving stations for responding by members of said audience to a task presented in a program; 
response evaluation means communicatively connected to said responding means responsive to said instructional signal, and including means for timing and means for scoring responses; 
wherein said scoring ranges from the simple comparison of a task to response criteria in order to determine an acceptable response accompanied by a fixed award to the computerized processing of acceptable responses in accordance with scoring instructions to determine computed awards; 
wherein said scoring instructions have been determined prior to the transmission of said program signal; 
wherein said program and said instructional signals provide information of said task-setting program signals, said information comprising at least one question which is either a single-part question or a multiple-part question; and 
means for informing members of said audience of an acceptable response and of a fixed or computed award therefor, said informing following the elapsing of at least a significant portion of said allowed time period; 
wherein, if two or more responses are acceptable, one can be a preferred response; 
wherein a preferred response receives a higher score award; 
wherein said evaluation means scores an individual response essentially immediately following its input by a member; and 
wherein said evaluation means permits input of a single response by a member on the spur of the moment.

