23. In a method for conducting an event in which successful participants who have acceptably responded to a question or made an acceptable prediction and who are rewarded with prizes having monetary value in the form of a token and the like dispensed to such successful participant, the improvement comprising the steps of: 
determining at a central location a monetary prize amount; 
upon issuance a prize in the form of a token, or the like, exceeding the determined amount, instituting a forgery resisting procedure comprising the steps of: 
recording on said token verification data, including an identification of the event which has resulted in said prize being won and in the dispensing of said token to a successful participant; 
communicating said verification data and event identification to a central data storage facility inaccessible to participants; 
upon presentation of one of said tokens by a participant for redemption or payment at a paying agent's location, contacting by said paying agent said central data storage facility requesting, authentication of said verification data; 
the central data storage facility authenticating said verification data; and 
said paying agent paying the amount of an authenticated prize to the presenting participant.

